The paper presents a new approach to compute the Dynamic Time Warping (DTW) distance between time series that is space-efficient and always yields the optimal result. This involves dynamically exploiting the existence of similarity and/or correlation between the time series. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
